cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.CY

The paper involves combining different data sets and using scientometric performance indicators to compare funding decisions in two fields of science (life sciences and social sciences). This suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) for managing and analyzing the data sets. The use of performance indicators also suggests a focus on computational science (cs.CR) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper involves comparing and evaluating research proposals, which could fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
